definitions: formal speech or written tribute given to honor someone who has recently died
examples: The minister delivered a touching eulogy at her funeral
He prepared a heartfelt eulogy for his late grandfather

definitions: man who has been castrated, especially one employed as a guard in harems
examples: The sultan's palace was guarded by trusted eunuchs
Eunuchs held important positions in ancient Chinese courts

definitions: mild or indirect word or expression substituted for one considered too harsh or direct
examples: Passed away is a common euphemism for died
The company used downsizing as a euphemism for layoffs

definitions: large brass wind instrument with valves, similar to a small tuba but higher in pitch
examples: She played the euphonium in the school marching band
The euphonium produces a rich, mellow tone in the brass section

definitions: feeling or state of intense excitement, happiness, and well-being that seems beyond normal
examples: Winning the championship filled the team with euphoria
She experienced a moment of pure euphoria after receiving the good news

definitions: official currency used by most countries in the European Union monetary system
examples: The hotel room costs fifty euros per night
She exchanged her dollars for euros at the airport

definitions: practice of intentionally ending life to relieve pain and suffering, especially for terminally ill patients
examples: The debate over euthanasia continues in many countries worldwide
Some veterinarians recommend euthanasia for severely suffering pets

definitions: organized removal of people from a dangerous place to somewhere safer during an emergency
examples: The fire alarm triggered an immediate evacuation of the building
Coastal residents prepared for evacuation as the hurricane approached

definitions: person who examines and judges the quality, importance, or value of something
examples: The evaluator carefully reviewed each student's performance
An independent evaluator assessed the program's effectiveness

definitions: quality of being fleeting or quickly fading away like vapor or smoke
examples: The evanescence of morning mist creates a mystical atmosphere
She captured the evanescence of childhood in her photographs

definitions: branch of Protestant Christianity emphasizing personal salvation through faith in Jesus Christ and the authority of the Bible
examples: Evangelicalism has grown significantly in Latin America
The church follows the core principles of modern evangelicalism

definitions: practice of spreading the Christian gospel by preaching or personal witness to convert others
examples: The church organized evangelism campaigns in local communities
Door-to-door evangelism remains common in some religious groups

definitions: person who seeks to convert others to Christianity through preaching
passionate advocate or promoter of a particular cause or belief
examples: The evangelist traveled from town to town preaching the gospel
Billy Graham was one of the most famous evangelists of the twentieth century
She became an evangelist for sustainable living practices
The CEO was an evangelist for digital transformation in business

definitions: process by which liquid water changes into water vapor and enters the atmosphere
examples: The hot sun increased the rate of evaporation from the lake
Evaporation is a crucial part of the water cycle

definitions: act of avoiding or escaping from something, especially a duty, question, or responsibility
examples: His constant evasion of direct questions frustrated the interviewer
Tax evasion can result in serious legal consequences

definitions: evening or day before a special event, holiday, or important occasion
examples: The family gathered together on Christmas Eve for dinner
Excitement filled the air on the eve of the election

definitions: church service of evening prayers, psalms, and canticles in Anglican and Episcopal traditions
examples: The cathedral choir performed beautifully during evensong
They attended evensong every Sunday at five o'clock

definitions: possible event or outcome that might happen in the future, especially an unpleasant one
examples: We must prepare for every eventuality during the storm
The insurance policy covers most eventualities that could occur

definitions: tree or shrub that keeps its green leaves throughout the year
something that remains fresh, interesting, or popular over a long time
examples: Pine trees are common evergreens in northern forests
The gardener planted evergreens to provide year-round color
That song remains an evergreen hit after fifty years
Classic movies are evergreen content for streaming platforms

definitions: something that lasts forever or for a very long time without ending
examples: Their promise of everlasting friendship touched everyone's hearts
The monument stands as an everlasting tribute to fallen soldiers

definitions: ordinary or typical person representing the common people in general
examples: The actor perfectly portrayed the everyman struggling with daily life
The story's everyman hero made it relatable to audiences

definitions: legal process of forcing someone to leave a property they are renting or occupying
examples: The landlord started eviction proceedings for non-payment of rent
Many families faced eviction during the economic downturn

definitions: act of bringing a feeling, memory, or image into the mind through description or suggestion
examples: The music's evocation of childhood summers brought tears to her eyes
His evocation of ancient Rome was vivid and compelling

definitions: adult female sheep, especially one kept for breeding or wool production
examples: The farmer separated the ewes from the rams
Each ewe in the flock produced two lambs this spring

definitions: act of representing something as larger, better, or worse than it really is
examples: His story about the fish was clearly an exaggeration
The media's exaggeration of the incident caused unnecessary panic

definitions: feeling of extreme happiness and excitement about something
act of raising someone or something to a higher rank or position of honor
examples: She felt pure exaltation when she received the acceptance letter
The crowd's exaltation was evident after the victory
The exaltation of the new saint took place in Rome
His exaltation to company president surprised many colleagues

definitions: person who conducts examinations or inspects something officially to assess quality or compliance
examples: The driving examiner noted every mistake during the test
Medical examiners determine the cause of suspicious deaths

definitions: act of removing earth carefully to find buried remains or to make a hole for construction
examples: The archaeological excavation revealed ancient pottery fragments
Construction crews began excavation for the new building's foundation

definitions: large machine with a bucket for digging and moving earth
person who excavates archaeological sites professionally
examples: The construction site used three excavators to clear the land
The excavator's bucket could move tons of dirt per hour
The lead excavator discovered the ancient tomb entrance
Experienced excavators know how to preserve delicate artifacts

definitions: quality of being outstanding or extremely good in performance, skill, or achievement
examples: The restaurant is known for its excellence in French cuisine
She received an award for academic excellence

definitions: formal title used to address high-ranking officials such as ambassadors, governors, or bishops
examples: Your Excellency, the ambassador has arrived for the meeting
His Excellency the Governor will speak at the ceremony

definitions: short extract or passage taken from a longer work such as a book, film, or piece of music
examples: The magazine published an excerpt from her upcoming novel
He read an excerpt from Shakespeare during the presentation

definitions: device that transfers heat or other properties between fluids
person who exchanges money or goods professionally
examples: The heat exchanger helps cool the engine efficiently
The air conditioning system needs a new heat exchanger
The currency exchanger offered competitive rates at the airport
Stock exchangers facilitate trades on the trading floor

definitions: royal or national treasury, especially in Britain, or the government department managing public revenue
examples: The Chancellor of the Exchequer announced the new budget
The exchequer faced a significant deficit this year

definitions: tax levied on certain goods and services produced or sold within a country
examples: The government increased the excise on tobacco products
Excise duties on alcohol generate significant revenue

definitions: act of cutting out or removing something, especially by surgery
examples: The surgeon performed an excision of the tumor
Complete excision of the damaged tissue was necessary

definitions: quality of being easily excited or aroused emotionally or physically
examples: The puppy's excitability made training sessions challenging
Nerve excitability can be affected by certain medications

definitions: state of being emotionally aroused or the process of stimulating something to a higher energy level
examples: The excitation of the crowd grew as the game intensified
Electrical excitation of neurons triggers nerve impulses

definitions: sudden cry or remark expressing surprise, strong emotion, or pain
examples: Her exclamation of joy could be heard across the room
The audience let out exclamations of amazement during the magic show

definitions: act of not allowing someone or something to participate or be included
examples: The exclusion of certain students from activities caused controversy
The insurance policy has several exclusions for pre-existing conditions

definitions: waste matter discharged from the bowels of humans or animals
examples: The veterinarian examined the animal's excrement for parasites
Bird excrement can damage car paint if not cleaned quickly

definitions: process by which metabolic waste is eliminated from an organism
examples: Kidney function is essential for proper excretion of toxins
The excretion of excess salt helps maintain body balance

definitions: short journey or trip, especially one taken for leisure or education
examples: The class took an excursion to the natural history museum
We booked a day excursion to the nearby islands

definitions: official who carries out a sentence of death on a condemned person
examples: The executioner wore a black hood to conceal his identity
Medieval executioners often served as the town's medical practitioners

definitions: person appointed to carry out the terms of a will after someone dies
examples: She named her eldest son as executor of her estate
The executor must distribute assets according to the will's instructions

definitions: person or thing serving as a typical example or excellent model of a quality
examples: She was an exemplar of courage during the crisis
This building serves as an exemplar of sustainable architecture

definitions: state of being free from an obligation or liability imposed on others
examples: Religious organizations often receive tax exemption status
He applied for exemption from military service
